reviews:
I must have at least 15 flashlights, mostly Fenix...Maybe it's just me but Fenix has fell behind in the lumens race...Not that lumens is necessarily the most important attribute of a light but when your highest lumen light for Fenix is 9K lumens and other quality brands are taunting 50-60K lumens, thats quite a difference.. And these aren't phony Chinese lumens as I call them, they are documented from reliable testing sources...

I consider the X45 to be the baby Imalent DX80...For those times when I don't want to lug around the DX80, the X45 is a perfect replacement...Mainly because the X45 has excellent throw and flood, just like the DX80...Only the run times are reduced because of half the batteries...I can use the X45 at 5000 lumens for a hour with no heat problem, which is huge for me...

Speaking of heat the little I've used an Acebeam X80 it seemed to get quite hot at 5000 lumens so that was turn off for me...The size and the wall of light by the X80 are wonderful but being so small it just doesn't handle even mid lumens very well without heating up to the point one needs gloves..Its all subjective but I prefer the X45 as it handles the heat so much better and 18K lumens is plenty for a smaller light..

Also, I like using the white diffuser screw on filter for the X45 as it really smooths out the light for lighting up a large enclosed area...

Not much else to say other than try one...

kd

review_title: Good light but value depends on what you use it for.
reviews:
I recently purchased an x45 from Amazon. The light came with 4 protected batteries one of which was defective. Amazon refunded me the cost of a replacement battery $16.75.
This light is well engineered but not well thought out. The x45 heats up quickly and can be uncomfortable to hold. The light is extremely bright on turbo settings. A bright light and brighter dog once saved my life from an assaliant poised to attack hidden in a tree line at night. Even with scorched eyes it took him 4 minutes to retreat.
Value comes down to what you want to use the light for. Utility as a dog walking light is low because of heat and short battery life. Utility as an S&R or a toy to light the night for short periods is high. Spare batteries? Be prepared to spend $65 to $85 for an extra set. Also, I would suggest a high end charger. A cheap charger might trip the circuit board in the protected batteries rendering them useless.
I would like to see a longer barrel using 22650 batteries, for better heat dissipation, baton use and longer run time. A shoulder strap would be a welcome addition. I modified my x45 to accept one. I would also like a tighter beam, the spill hits my neighbor's homes on both sides of the road. Hence I keep the light pointed almost straight down to avoid disturbing them. I do like the x45.

reviews:
I have several high end flashlights and this is my first 4000 lumen plus light and this thing does not disappoint!!!
Lights I compared the x45 to
-Nitecore TM26gt 3500lumens
-Olight SR mini intimidator ii 3200lumens
-Nitecore TM03 2800lumens
I have many more but none of my lights have close to this output which looks to be around 14,900 lumens NOTE IT DOESNT SAY WHAT TINT YOU WILL RECIEVE well not where I have seen but I received the 5000k tint and it looks nice.
Just to try it I threw some unprotected Samsung 2000mah batteries in and they did well just bad run times but they handled the load fine.
I did not buy this light for the 16500 lumens I just simply love lights and wanted one that could maintain 4000 lumens without a step down after a couple of minutes and this does that. Now to the company ACEBEAM perfect light besides in my opinion missing two things
1. WOULD LOVE BUILT IN CHARGING
2. THE OPTION OF A BATTERY PACK LIKE THE X65 would be amazing but a slightly smaller one maybe so it is more affordable

Hope this review helped someone in some way this thing puts all sub 9000 lumen lights to shame the price is perfect !!!! May even buy another in the cool white tint if possible oh and THANK YOU GOING GEAR FOR HAVING PRODUCTS ON AMAZON WILL BUY FROM YOU MUCH MORE OFTEN NOW !!!!!

review_title: It will blind you, 18000 Lumens get hot. But a Fun Toy.
reviews: I like this flashlight. Its not for the average person, but it performs just what it was designed for. Using it in turbo mode is an excellent, bright light in a short period, for searching, its great. I tested the batteries with OBUS BT- 3400 before using them, and they came in at 2900 milliamps, which is right in range. I did strobe mode on a white ceiling and for a short time, and I saw four led blue dots because of the brightness. For spare batteries, get protected high output because the light demands it. Nobody needs any more Lumens than this light. The light will get too hot over three minutes. I do like this light for showing off.
